

==Greek==
===Prefix===
'''α-''' before [[consonant]]s and '''αν-''' before [[vowel]]s
# [[a-]], [[an-]]
# The [[alpha privativum]], used to make words that have a sense [[opposite]] to the word (or [[stem]]) to which the [[prefix]] is attached. It is also known as [[privative a]] and [[alpha privative]].
# (In ancient greek) The [[alpha copulativum]], used to express unity, eg. in '''α-''' δελφός "brother" literally "from the same womb". Also known as [[copulative a]] and [[a athroistikon]].

